59:20.040 --> 59:23.555
Well, you just let Rowena
take care of everything, honey.

59:23.680 --> 59:27.639
All you gotta do is put
your arms around me. Come on.

59:29.320 --> 59:31.276
That's it.

59:36.200 --> 59:40.079
There, now, you're doin' fine.

59:40.200 --> 59:42.589
- You got your knee on my stomach.
- I'm sorry.

59:42.720 --> 59:44.915
Let's get those shorts off.

59:45.040 --> 59:48.237
That's better. Now, isn't that better?

59:48.360 --> 59:50.999
Oh. Oh, God!

59:51.120 --> 59:52.712
Oh!

59:52.840 --> 59:53.909
Oh, God!

59:54.040 --> 59:56.395
Relax, hon. Nothin' to it, sugar.

59:56.520 --> 59:59.273
You're not breathin'. Breathe!

59:59.400 --> 01:00:01.311
My nose is running.

01:00:01.440 --> 01:00:03.271
No, I'm OK.

01:00:03.400 --> 01:00:05.834
Don't stop, baby, you're gettin' there.

01:00:05.960 --> 01:00:07.313
Oh.

01:00:07.440 --> 01:00:09.032
Oh, jeez.

01:00:09.160 --> 01:00:10.798
Oh, my God!

01:00:10.920 --> 01:00:13.070
Oh. Oh...

01:00:14.920 --> 01:00:17.480
You did it, babe!

01:00:17.600 --> 01:00:19.875
I did it. I did it.

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:20.876
(# jazz tune)

01:00:28.200 --> 01:00:30.760
- Not too close, please.
- Oh, forgive me.

01:00:34.120 --> 01:00:38.955
- You girls always wear white gloves?
- It's proper attire for a lady at a dance.

01:00:39.080 --> 01:00:42.072
In the old days a man would
hold a handkerchief in his hand...

01:00:42.200 --> 01:00:44.634
..so as not to touch
the bare back of his partner.

01:00:44.760 --> 01:00:47.718
No kiddin'? Next time
I'll come here in a tank.

01:00:52.240 --> 01:00:55.312
You can't get near these girls
unless you're a priest.

01:00:55.440 --> 01:00:56.998
Aw, who wants to?

01:00:57.120 --> 01:01:00.271
- Nothin' better than what we had. Right?
- Right, yeah.

01:01:00.400 --> 01:01:03.358
That Rowena's a real
roller coaster, ain't she?

01:01:05.840 --> 01:01:07.432
Hey, there.

01:01:07.560 --> 01:01:09.516
(clicks tongue)

01:01:10.640 --> 01:01:13.029
- Hey. Hi, guys, what's cookin'?
- How'd it go?

01:01:13.160 --> 01:01:16.357
How'd it go? It was fine as wine.
Sorta chatty, know what I mean?

01:01:16.480 --> 01:01:19.040
Chatty? First time
in the sack with a pro was chatty?

01:01:19.160 --> 01:01:21.879
Real smooth. Second time
was swing, swing, swing.

01:01:22.000 --> 01:01:25.959
- Second time? You paid twice?
- No, it was a freebie. On the house.

01:01:26.080 --> 01:01:30.915
- Why would she give you a free one?
- Maybe I was her one millionth customer.

01:01:31.040 --> 01:01:32.996
Think I'll look around.

01:01:35.240 --> 01:01:36.992
Bullshit artist.

01:01:37.120 --> 01:01:39.076
Let's get outta here.

01:01:48.760 --> 01:01:50.716
(# jazz tune ends)

01:01:54.720 --> 01:01:56.676
(# slow tune starts)

01:01:57.640 --> 01:01:59.596
Would you care to dance?

01:02:01.240 --> 01:02:04.516
- What?
- I said would you care to dance?

01:02:05.080 --> 01:02:07.799
Oh. I don't dance very well.

01:02:07.920 --> 01:02:11.674
- I bet you do.
- No, I swear. I never dance.

01:02:11.800 --> 01:02:15.634
- Then why did you come to a dance?
- It's a good question.

01:02:15.760 --> 01:02:17.751
I like to listen to music...

01:02:17.880 --> 01:02:22.158
..and I was hoping that I'd meet
somebody I could talk to. I like to talk.

01:02:23.080 --> 01:02:25.310
Well, we could talk while we dance.

01:02:27.400 --> 01:02:29.550
OK. Sure.

01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:34.636
Watch your toes.

01:02:39.720 --> 01:02:41.676
Well, you're doin' fine.

01:02:43.000 --> 01:02:45.594
- Are you countin'?
- A little.

01:02:45.720 --> 01:02:47.836
I can see your lips movin'.

01:02:47.960 --> 01:02:50.713
My lips don't move, my feet don't move.

01:02:53.200 --> 01:02:55.919
- Is that perfume you're wearin'?
- Perfume?

01:02:57.240 --> 01:02:59.276
It's ladies' perfume.

01:02:59.400 --> 01:03:02.312
I smelt it before.
Two of the other soldiers had it on.

01:03:02.440 --> 01:03:06.228
Oh, yeah. It's... it's for my mother.

01:03:06.360 --> 01:03:09.113
The lady on the counter sprayed it on me.

01:03:10.160 --> 01:03:12.230
Do you think it's too strong?

01:03:12.360 --> 01:03:16.478
Well, yours is a little different.
Yours has a little Aqua velva in it.

01:03:16.600 --> 01:03:19.160
Well, that's me underneath.

01:03:19.280 --> 01:03:22.909
- What's your name?
- Eugene Morris Jerome.

01:03:23.040 --> 01:03:26.032
If you want the short version, it's Eugene.

01:03:26.160 --> 01:03:29.675
- What's your name?
- Daisy. Daisy Hannigan.

01:03:29.800 --> 01:03:33.554
Dai... No kiddin'? That's a beautiful name.

01:03:34.400 --> 01:03:37.073
Daisy is my favourite character
in literature.

01:03:37.200 --> 01:03:40.476
- Daisy Miller or Daisy Buchanan?
- Buchanan.

01:03:40.600 --> 01:03:44.229
The Great Gatsby is one of
my all-time favourite books.

01:03:44.360 --> 01:03:48.512
- I've never read Daisy Miller. Is it good?
- Oh, it's wonderful.

01:03:48.640 --> 01:03:52.633
You look surprised.
We do read in the South, you know.

01:03:52.760 --> 01:03:54.830
I know.

01:03:54.960 --> 01:03:57.713
- You have a funny look on your face.
- I do?

01:03:57.840 --> 01:03:59.432
Uh-huh.

01:03:59.560 --> 01:04:01.835
It's like a birthday look.

01:04:01.960 --> 01:04:04.520
- Today isn't your birthday, is it?
- No.

01:04:05.720 --> 01:04:08.712
Something special
happened to you today, am I right?

01:04:08.840 --> 01:04:10.398
Yeah.

01:04:10.520 --> 01:04:13.876
- Can you tell me about it?
- I don't think so.

01:04:15.760 --> 01:04:19.355
- I might put it in my memoirs, though.
- Oh.

01:04:19.480 --> 01:04:23.439
- Do you keep a journal every day?
- Yes. Since I was 14.

01:04:23.560 --> 01:04:26.233
I write down everything
that happens to me.

01:04:26.360 --> 01:04:30.319
- Do you like writin'?
- Yeah. It's what I hope to be one day.

01:04:32.480 --> 01:04:34.755
Will you write about
dancin' with me tonight?

01:04:34.880 --> 01:04:37.348
Yeah, probably.

01:04:37.480 --> 01:04:42.838
Great. Then if you ever become
a famous writer, I'll be immortalised!

01:04:43.840 --> 01:04:46.400
(# "How High the Moon" by Pat Suzuki)

01:04:55.920 --> 01:05:03.508
# Somewhere there's music

01:05:03.640 --> 01:05:10.876
# How faint the tune

01:05:12.240 --> 01:05:18.873
# Somewhere there's heaven

01:05:19.000 --> 01:05:26.350
# How high the moon

01:05:27.640 --> 01:05:32.430
# There is no moon above

01:05:33.200 --> 01:05:42.472
# When love is far away, too

01:05:42.600 --> 01:05:49.073
# Till it comes true

01:05:49.200 --> 01:05:53.671
# That you love me

01:05:53.800 --> 01:05:57.156
# As I love you

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:04.155
# Somewhere there's music

01:06:05.320 --> 01:06:11.793
# lt's where you are...

01:06:11.920 --> 01:06:14.229
The sisters are lookin' at me.

01:06:14.360 --> 01:06:17.591
We're not allowed to spend
too much time with one boy.

01:06:17.720 --> 01:06:22.111
The song isn't over yet.
I'm entitled to one song, right?

01:06:22.240 --> 01:06:25.596
Can l... You want me
to get you a Coke or something?

01:06:27.040 --> 01:06:29.156
It's way on the other side of the room.

01:06:29.280 --> 01:06:31.475
The song would be over
when you got back.

01:06:31.600 --> 01:06:34.558
Yeah. Let the next guy get you a Coke.

01:06:36.600 --> 01:06:40.479
- Do you live in Biloxi?
- No. We go to school in Gulfport.

01:06:40.600 --> 01:06:44.639
Gulfport, really? No kidding?
I know a girl from Gulfport.

01:06:44.760 --> 01:06:47.558
Really? Who is she? Maybe I know her.

01:06:47.680 --> 01:06:50.148
Oh, no, I don't think so.

01:06:50.280 --> 01:06:52.635
She's in the clothing business.

01:06:54.720 --> 01:06:57.075
Well, I really have to go.

01:06:58.280 --> 01:07:00.840
It was very nice meetin' you, Eugene.

01:07:03.160 --> 01:07:05.754
Are you gonna be
back here next weekend?

01:07:05.880 --> 01:07:08.792
No, we only come in once a month.

01:07:08.920 --> 01:07:11.480
Maybe I could come out to Gulfport.

01:07:12.400 --> 01:07:15.358
Well, we're really
not allowed to make dates.

01:07:15.480 --> 01:07:19.598
Well, it wouldn't be a date
if I was just to bump into you, would it?

01:07:19.720 --> 01:07:22.473
Well, it would be if I went to confession.

01:07:23.800 --> 01:07:28.476
Especially if I told you I went
to St Mary's on Piermont Street.

01:07:28.600 --> 01:07:30.955
- Goodbye, Eugene.
- Goodbye, Daisy.

01:07:32.360 --> 01:07:37.309
Eugene, you didn't say one wrong thing
in that whole conversation.

01:07:48.200 --> 01:07:49.952
Ever have one of those perfect days?

01:08:16.880 --> 01:08:20.429
I can't believe what this creep's
been writin' about us.

01:08:21.319 --> 01:08:23.276
Listen to this.

01:08:24.359 --> 01:08:27.477
"No matter how lunatic
I think Sergeant Toomey is,...

01:08:27.600 --> 01:08:29.750
..each day he goes a little further."

01:08:29.880 --> 01:08:35.716
"Yesterday he made Epstein unscrew the
top of this head and take his brains out."

01:08:35.840 --> 01:08:38.832
I fooled him. I only took out
my mucous membranes.

01:08:39.760 --> 01:08:41.716
Hubba, hubba!

01:08:43.319 --> 01:08:45.550
What a weekend. What did you guys do?

01:08:45.680 --> 01:08:50.117
- Hennesey, listen. You're in this, too.
- Yeah, what is it?

01:08:50.240 --> 01:08:53.595
"The Secret and Private Memoirs
of Eugene M Jerome."

01:08:55.600 --> 01:08:56.953
He let you read that?

01:08:57.080 --> 01:08:59.877
No. We'll ask him if it's all right
when we get through.

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:02.514
When we get through!

01:09:02.640 --> 01:09:05.029
You have no right.
It's like opening his mail.

01:09:05.160 --> 01:09:10.439
Bullshit! It's private things about all of us.
It's public domain like in the newspapers.

01:09:10.560 --> 01:09:14.678
Newspapers are published. Unpublished
memoirs are the writer's sole property.

01:09:14.800 --> 01:09:19.032
You know, I thought all Jews were doctors.
I didn't know they were lawyers, too.

01:09:19.160 --> 01:09:21.912
- I'm not a Jew any more, Wykowski.
- What do you mean?

01:09:22.040 --> 01:09:24.600
I converted to Catholicism yesterday.

01:09:24.720 --> 01:09:27.234
In six weeks I hope to become a priest.

01:09:27.359 --> 01:09:31.478
And my first act of service to the Holy
Father is to have you excommunicated,...

01:09:31.600 --> 01:09:33.555
..so get off my ass.

01:09:34.920 --> 01:09:37.832
That's good. That's funny.
He got you that time, 'Kowski.

01:09:37.960 --> 01:09:39.756
Shut up!

01:09:39.880 --> 01:09:42.553
I thought you were
Eugene's friend, Epstein.

01:09:42.680 --> 01:09:47.071
He left his locker open. Why'd he leave
something so private in an open locker?

01:09:47.200 --> 01:09:50.715
It has no logic to it.
I have no interest in illogical things.

01:09:50.840 --> 01:09:54.310
Well, you tell Gene I had
nothin' to do with this, you hear?

01:09:54.440 --> 01:09:56.396
Go on, keep readin'.

01:09:57.520 --> 01:10:02.071
"One night a sudden scream from
Selridge calling out the name Louise."

01:10:02.200 --> 01:10:04.839
"Is Louise his girlfriend or his mother?"

01:10:04.960 --> 01:10:08.316
- He's full of crap!
- Yeah, well, who's Louise?

01:10:08.440 --> 01:10:12.513
My mother. But he's full of it.
I never called my mother Louise.

01:10:12.640 --> 01:10:14.676
Poor baby wants his mother.

01:10:14.800 --> 01:10:16.756
Hey, it's him.

01:10:20.840 --> 01:10:23.593
Two in one day. Two in one day.
Can you believe it?

01:10:23.720 --> 01:10:26.154
- Two what?
- Two fantasies came true.

01:10:26.280 --> 01:10:29.397
- I lost my virginity and I fell in love.
- With Rowena?

01:10:29.520 --> 01:10:31.636
I can't wait for her to meet your parents.

01:10:31.760 --> 01:10:34.593
Her name is Daisy. Daisy Hannigan.

01:10:34.720 --> 01:10:37.678
Every time I say it
I get tiny little heart attacks.

01:10:37.800 --> 01:10:41.998
Not enough to kill ya. Just enough
to keep you from walking straight.

01:10:44.960 --> 01:10:46.712
Hey.

01:10:47.520 --> 01:10:51.069
- Anybody seen my notebook?
- What notebook is that?

01:10:53.360 --> 01:10:55.715
The one I'm always writing in.

01:10:57.120 --> 01:10:59.076
Arnold, have you seen it?

01:11:00.320 --> 01:11:02.880
Why did you leave your locker open?

01:11:03.920 --> 01:11:07.151
Because I lost the key
down the shower drain.

01:11:07.280 --> 01:11:10.670
There was nothing valuable
in there except my notebook.

01:11:10.800 --> 01:11:12.916
I thought I could trust the guys here.

01:11:13.040 --> 01:11:16.476
Hey, that's funny, Jerome,
cos we thought we could trust you, too.

01:11:16.600 --> 01:11:18.556
What does that mean?

01:11:21.440 --> 01:11:23.476
"One night a scream from Selridge...

01:11:23.600 --> 01:11:25.670
- Hey! Gimme that!
- ..calling out Louise!"

01:11:25.800 --> 01:11:28.837
- "Is Louise his girlfriend or mother?"
- You have no right!

01:11:28.960 --> 01:11:32.316
Yeah? And you got no business
writing down my dreams.

01:11:32.440 --> 01:11:36.194
- Give it back. Nobody is interested.
- Not even in what he thinks about you?

01:11:36.320 --> 01:11:40.518
- Give it to me!
- You want an arm broken, it's up to you.

01:11:40.640 --> 01:11:44.394
- 'Kowski, please don't read that.
- If it gets boring, I'll stop.

01:11:44.520 --> 01:11:48.593
"I can't make Don Carney out yet.
Basically he's OK and I like him."

01:11:50.680 --> 01:11:53.513
"But there's something
about him you can't count on,...

01:11:53.640 --> 01:11:58.191
..and if I was ever in real trouble
Don Carney's the last one I'd turn to."

01:12:00.680 --> 01:12:05.037
Well... Iet's just hope
you don't have to count on me.

01:12:05.160 --> 01:12:07.071
It doesn't mean anything.

01:12:07.200 --> 01:12:10.158
- I get a thought and I write it down.
- Let him go, Selridge.

01:12:10.280 --> 01:12:12.840
Wanna take his place?
I don't care whose arm I break.

01:12:12.960 --> 01:12:16.396
OK, you ready for the best part?
Here's the best part.

01:12:16.520 --> 01:12:18.476
"Wykowski is pure animal."

01:12:19.360 --> 01:12:23.035
"He masturbates in bed
four or five times a night."

01:12:23.160 --> 01:12:26.994
"He has no shame about it
and his capacities are enormous."

01:12:27.120 --> 01:12:30.237
"sometimes when he has a discharge
he announces it to the room:

01:12:30.360 --> 01:12:33.750
"Number five torpedo fired,
loading number six."'

01:12:33.880 --> 01:12:36.838
Hey, Epstein,
can I sue him for defamation of...

01:12:37.440 --> 01:12:38.998
- What is it?
- Character?

01:12:39.120 --> 01:12:43.193
Only if his intent is to prove malice,
and in your case it's not possible.

01:12:43.320 --> 01:12:45.276
- Read more.
- Where was l?

01:12:45.400 --> 01:12:48.153
You just fired number five.

01:12:48.280 --> 01:12:51.750
"Despite Wykowski's
lack of culture, sensitivity...

01:12:51.880 --> 01:12:54.758
..or the pursuit of
anything minutely intellectual,...

01:12:54.880 --> 01:13:00.557
..his greatest strength is his earnest
belief that he belongs on the battlefield."

01:13:00.680 --> 01:13:03.433
"He is clearly the best soldier in the pl...

01:13:05.000 --> 01:13:07.434
..in the platoon,
dependable under pressure."

01:13:07.560 --> 01:13:12.509
"It wouldn't surprise me if Wykowski came
out of the war with the Medal of Honor."

01:13:14.080 --> 01:13:16.150
You really mean that, Jerome?

01:13:16.280 --> 01:13:18.510
I told you, I don't mean any of it.

01:13:18.640 --> 01:13:21.837
Right now I would describe you
in three words: a yellow bastard!

01:13:21.960 --> 01:13:26.988
Yeah, well, they don't give the Medal of
Honor to yellow bastards. Let him go, Sel.

01:13:33.120 --> 01:13:36.476
What do you write this down for?
You'll make a lotta guys unhappy.

01:13:36.600 --> 01:13:39.433
What I write in my book
is my business. Give it to me.

01:13:39.560 --> 01:13:42.358
Don't I get to hear my life story?

01:13:42.480 --> 01:13:44.948
Arnold, I beg you!

01:13:45.080 --> 01:13:46.957
Don't read that!

01:13:47.080 --> 01:13:49.514
They're my private thoughts!

01:13:49.640 --> 01:13:53.189
- If you take them, you steal from me.
- I gather it's unflattering.

01:13:53.320 --> 01:13:57.598
Don't you know me by now, Gene?
I can't be unflattered. I'm past it.

01:13:57.720 --> 01:14:00.712
However, if you don't want me
to read it, I won't read it.

01:14:00.840 --> 01:14:05.516
But I don't think we'll be able to be
truly honest with each other from now on.

01:14:10.680 --> 01:14:13.240
Put it back when you're through.

01:14:14.720 --> 01:14:16.676
(clears throat)

01:14:17.600 --> 01:14:19.556
Well, don't we get to hear it?

01:14:28.880 --> 01:14:34.318
"Arnold Epstein's constant pursuit of
truth, logic and reason fascinates me...

01:14:34.440 --> 01:14:37.796
..in the same proportion as
his obstinacy and unnecessary heroics...

01:14:37.920 --> 01:14:39.876
..drive me to distraction."

01:14:41.240 --> 01:14:44.789
"But I love him for it, in the same
manner that I love Joe DiMaggio...

01:14:44.920 --> 01:14:48.959
..for making the gesture
of catching a long fly ball to centre."

01:14:49.080 --> 01:14:53.073
"seemed like the last miracle
performed by God in modern times."

01:14:54.280 --> 01:14:57.636
"But often I hold back showing
my love and affection for Arnold...

01:14:57.760 --> 01:15:00.672
..because I think he might misinterpret it."

01:15:00.800 --> 01:15:04.952
"It just happens to be
my instinctive feeling that Arnold...

01:15:07.120 --> 01:15:09.076
..is...

01:15:10.280 --> 01:15:12.236
..homosexual,...

01:15:12.360 --> 01:15:15.113
..and it bothers me that it bothers me."

01:15:22.080 --> 01:15:24.036
(bugle sounds the retreat)

01:15:30.960 --> 01:15:33.872
Do you see why I find life so interesting?

01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:39.154
Because here is a man who in three weeks
has come to the brilliant conclusion...

01:15:39.280 --> 01:15:42.556
..that a cretin like Wykowski
is going to win the Medal of Honor...

01:15:42.680 --> 01:15:46.434
..and that his most esteemed
and dearest friend is a fairy.

01:15:48.280 --> 01:15:50.236
(Toomey) Lights out!

01:16:13.800 --> 01:16:18.749
It is my opinion that no one here gets
a wink of sleep tonight. Good night, fellas.

